733
00:28:41,842 --> 00:28:44,392
if I'd stayed here
like I wanted to instead of...

734
00:28:44,487 --> 00:28:47,021
letting you convince
me to go party.

735
00:28:50,139 --> 00:28:52,985
Hold on a second.
You're saying this is my fault?

736
00:28:53,711 --> 00:28:56,174
Because I didn't convince you,
I invited you.

737
00:28:56,261 --> 00:28:59,265
And you said you wanted an
associate who would push back.

738
00:28:59,306 --> 00:29:02,686
Push back on case work.
Not tell me not to do my job.

739
00:29:02,727 --> 00:29:04,178
Then let me push back right now,

740
00:29:04,219 --> 00:29:05,847
because you bluff these guys,

741
00:29:05,888 --> 00:29:07,850
you're opening yourself up
to huge exposure.

742
00:29:07,983 --> 00:29:09,155
So what?

743
00:29:09,477 --> 00:29:11,105
Harvey Specter
bluffs all the time.

744
00:29:11,146 --> 00:29:13,905
Harvey Specter has
a 15-plus-year track record

745
00:29:13,946 --> 00:29:15,490
of kicking people's asses.

746
00:29:16,259 --> 00:29:17,992
So you don't have faith in me
to pull this off.

747
00:29:18,032 --> 00:29:18,936
I didn't say that.

748
00:29:18,977 --> 00:29:21,392
I'm saying it's not a risk
worth taking,

749
00:29:21,433 --> 00:29:23,186
and I'm not gonna let you do it.

750
00:29:23,227 --> 00:29:25,898
Well, Brian,
there's a time to push back

751
00:29:25,939 --> 00:29:27,334
and a time to get in line.

752
00:29:27,375 --> 00:29:28,918
I'm going there
at 3 p.m. today,

753
00:29:28,959 --> 00:29:31,113
and you are either
with me or you're not.

754
00:29:31,154 --> 00:29:32,448
Then I'm not,

755
00:29:32,489 --> 00:29:35,411
because this is a mistake,
and you know it.

756
00:29:43,429 --> 00:29:44,973
Harvey, you have a minute?

757
00:29:45,014 --> 00:29:46,726
I'm about to file a few motions.

758
00:29:46,767 --> 00:29:48,058
But, yeah, I have a minute.

759
00:29:48,099 --> 00:29:49,397
I was under the impression

760
00:29:49,438 --> 00:29:50,809
you don't normally file
your own motions.

761
00:29:50,849 --> 00:29:53,269
Well, it's kind of important.
What's on your mind?

762
00:29:53,514 --> 00:29:55,059
Trouble in senior partner town?

763
00:29:55,278 --> 00:29:56,572
How'd you know?

764
00:29:56,613 --> 00:29:57,958
Because that's the first thing
that happens

765
00:29:57,998 --> 00:29:59,832
after you make it
to senior partner town.

766
00:30:01,379 --> 00:30:03,634
Well, then, long story short,

767
00:30:04,016 --> 00:30:07,082
it's my first case,
my back's against the wall,

768
00:30:07,123 --> 00:30:09,173
and my only way out is to bluff.

769
00:30:09,311 --> 00:30:11,034
- But?
- I'm opening myself up

770
00:30:11,099 --> 00:30:12,511
to significant exposure,

771
00:30:12,552 --> 00:30:13,879
and...

772
00:30:14,097 --> 00:30:16,535
I'm not sure I can pull it off.

773
00:30:17,504 --> 00:30:19,352
Then think of another way out.

774
00:30:19,494 --> 00:30:20,560
How come?

775
00:30:20,813 --> 00:30:23,571
Because if you're not sure
you can pull it off, you won't.

776
00:30:23,612 --> 00:30:25,449
And Katrina, life is long.

777
00:30:25,503 --> 00:30:28,341
You don't want to start senior
partnership with exposure.

778
00:30:28,382 --> 00:30:30,633
Now... I got to go.

779
00:30:31,655 --> 00:30:33,191
Thank you, Harvey.

780
00:30:40,025 --> 00:30:43,156
I see they're letting
you use your old office.

781
00:30:43,886 --> 00:30:45,855
First Robert, now you.

782
00:30:45,896 --> 00:30:47,541
Well, he had his turn at bat.

783
00:30:47,582 --> 00:30:49,308
We thought it was time
for me to have mine.

784
00:30:49,349 --> 00:30:50,727
Go ahead, take your best shot.

785
00:30:50,768 --> 00:30:52,298
Like I told Robert,

786
00:30:52,438 --> 00:30:53,147
I'm not bluffing.

787
00:30:53,188 --> 00:30:54,524
That's the thing, Tommy.

788
00:30:54,565 --> 00:30:56,793
We know you're not.
We figured out why.

789
00:30:56,834 --> 00:30:58,411
You don't know what
you're talking about.

790
00:30:58,451 --> 00:31:00,163
Yes, I do.

791
00:31:00,658 --> 00:31:03,663
Turns out three months ago,
you were diagnosed with cancer

792
00:31:03,704 --> 00:31:05,082
and given a year to live.

793
00:31:05,123 --> 00:31:07,293
Well, if you know that,
then you also know

794
00:31:07,334 --> 00:31:08,613
I'm never going to settle.

795
00:31:08,654 --> 00:31:12,243
What I know is what our
trial strategy's gonna be.

796
00:31:12,284 --> 00:31:13,913
Motion to delay,

797
00:31:14,430 --> 00:31:15,746
motion to delay,

798
00:31:15,787 --> 00:31:17,207
motion to delay.

799
00:31:17,248 --> 00:31:19,727
The wheels of justice
turn slowly, Tommy.

800
00:31:19,768 --> 00:31:22,585
Which means even if you win,
you won't be here to see it.

801
00:31:22,626 --> 00:31:24,602
You really are a son
of a bitch, aren't you?

802
00:31:24,643 --> 00:31:26,121
No. You did this.

803
00:31:26,162 --> 00:31:29,503
You brought this on yourself.
It's time to let it go.

804
00:31:29,544 --> 00:31:32,501
Spend what time you have left
with your family.

805
00:31:32,762 --> 00:31:35,517
Just let me go back to my firm
for nine months more,

806
00:31:35,558 --> 00:31:36,621
and I will drop this.

807
00:31:36,662 --> 00:31:39,602
I can't let you do that
because I've seen what you do.

808
00:31:39,855 --> 00:31:42,026
I'm not gonna let you
get back in the game

809
00:31:42,067 --> 00:31:44,095
and do something like this
to someone else.

810
00:31:44,896 --> 00:31:46,109
Then you know what?

811
00:31:46,165 --> 00:31:47,828
Delay all you want.

812
00:31:48,032 --> 00:31:50,828
Because they say when you're
fighting something like I am,

813
00:31:50,869 --> 00:31:52,747
you have to have something
to live for.

814
00:31:52,788 --> 00:31:55,584
Well, you just gave me two years
to live on hate alone.

815
00:31:55,625 --> 00:31:58,422
Now, get the hell out of here,
and I'll see you in court.

816
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:13,206
That looks like a job
for your associate.

817
00:32:13,394 --> 00:32:15,332
If you're just here
to talk me out of my bluff,

818
00:32:15,373 --> 00:32:16,942
you don't have to worry.
I'm not gonna do it.

819
00:32:16,982 --> 00:32:17,982
Good.

820
00:32:18,611 --> 00:32:20,595
Because you don't have to.

821
00:32:29,510 --> 00:32:30,972
I don't believe it.

822
00:32:31,259 --> 00:32:34,353
You got proof they colluded
with our manufacturer.

823
00:32:34,394 --> 00:32:35,738
I did.

824
00:32:36,282 --> 00:32:37,883
Brian, how did you get this?

825
00:32:37,924 --> 00:32:39,566
Simple. I called up the factory,

826
00:32:39,607 --> 00:32:42,802
pretending to be in Hi-Rise's
contracts department

827
00:32:42,843 --> 00:32:44,688
and started complaining
about how all we had

828
00:32:44,729 --> 00:32:47,602
were verbal assurances
they'd uphold our agreement.

829
00:32:47,651 --> 00:32:50,280
Eventually, they agreed
to sign a memo.

830
00:32:50,438 --> 00:32:52,365
They agreed to
incriminate themselves?

831
00:32:52,446 --> 00:32:56,425
Not exactly. I told them copyright
laws are notoriously vague,

832
00:32:56,466 --> 00:32:58,511
so their memo could be too.

833
00:32:58,567 --> 00:33:02,183
But even a vague memo is enough
for us to get them investigated.

834
00:33:02,224 --> 00:33:03,601
Or threaten to.

835
00:33:04,166 --> 00:33:05,454
But now...

836
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:07,798
you can do it with proof.

837
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:10,816
Did it occur to you

838
00:33:10,857 --> 00:33:12,738
that misrepresenting yourself
like this

839
00:33:12,779 --> 00:33:14,722
could have opened you up
to huge exposure?

840
00:33:14,903 --> 00:33:16,364
It did.

841
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:18,527
But I decided
it was worth the risk.

842
00:33:18,568 --> 00:33:21,277
Because my job may be
to push back,

843
00:33:21,318 --> 00:33:23,644
but it's also to have your back.

844
00:33:24,798 --> 00:33:26,823
And from now on, I will.

845
00:33:30,483 --> 00:33:33,063
Two more years on hate alone.

846
00:33:34,104 --> 00:33:35,253
He said that?

847
00:33:35,294 --> 00:33:37,923
He not only said it,
the son of a bitch meant it.

848
00:33:37,964 --> 00:33:40,510
He's gonna fight us
until his last breath.

849
00:33:41,425 --> 00:33:42,542
What?

850
00:33:43,092 --> 00:33:46,263
A man gets told he only has so
much time left on this earth,

851
00:33:46,304 --> 00:33:48,325
you would think that would
put things in perspective.

852
00:33:48,365 --> 00:33:49,826
You would.

853
00:33:50,666 --> 00:33:52,909
But I guess
he'd have to be human.

854
00:33:54,144 --> 00:33:57,543
And as it turns out,
he was more like the Terminator.

855
00:33:57,584 --> 00:33:59,421
Just won't go down.

856
00:33:59,733 --> 00:34:02,779
Come with me if you want to live.

857
00:34:02,820 --> 00:34:04,782
I'll be back.

858
00:34:04,823 --> 00:34:08,055
Hasta la vista, baby.

859
00:34:08,622 --> 00:34:10,578
If it bleeds, we can kill it.

860
00:34:10,619 --> 00:34:11,955
First of all, that's Predator.

861
00:34:11,995 --> 00:34:13,751
Second of all,
you sound Jamaican.

862
00:34:13,829 --> 00:34:14,960
Not German.

863
00:34:15,025 --> 00:34:17,601
Oh, man. Get off my back, man.

864
00:34:17,670 --> 00:34:19,679
You know what?
He's Austrian.

865
00:34:21,864 --> 00:34:23,220
Yeah.

866
00:34:27,346 --> 00:34:28,766
What are we gonna do?

867
00:34:29,323 --> 00:34:30,913
We're gonna do what we have to.

868
00:34:31,510 --> 00:34:33,437
We're gonna delay this
as long as possible,

869
00:34:33,478 --> 00:34:34,953
and then fight it on its merits.

870
00:34:34,994 --> 00:34:37,078
We don't have to
fight anything anymore.

871
00:34:37,909 --> 00:34:39,734
Tommy Bratton's dead.

872
00:34:40,639 --> 00:34:41,684
What?

873
00:34:41,725 --> 00:34:43,270
Eli Gould just called.

874
00:34:43,311 --> 00:34:45,064
He said Tommy
had a heart attack.

875
00:34:46,126 --> 00:34:49,276
They think it was brought on by the
stress of fighting his illness.

876
00:34:49,561 --> 00:34:51,520
And fighting us.

877
00:34:52,635 --> 00:34:54,431
Anyway, for what it's worth,

878
00:34:54,472 --> 00:34:56,118
Gould's dropping
the whole thing.

879
00:34:56,811 --> 00:34:58,541
I gotta say, I
always thought we'd win.

880
00:34:58,581 --> 00:34:59,959
But not like this.

881
00:35:00,385 --> 00:35:02,302
Robert, you okay?

882
00:35:04,121 --> 00:35:05,498
I don't know.

883
00:35:07,868 --> 00:35:10,165
We may have been at war, but...

884
00:35:10,695 --> 00:35:13,299
I knew the man for 30 years.

885
00:35:17,119 --> 00:35:19,673
I could use a minute
to process this.

886
00:35:21,527 --> 00:35:23,741
You take all the time you need.

887
00:35:37,133 --> 00:35:38,414
How'd it go?

888
00:35:40,792 --> 00:35:42,420
I didn't know you like baseball.

889
00:35:42,461 --> 00:35:44,423
I didn't know you like music.

890
00:35:44,860 --> 00:35:46,152
You heading home for the night?

891
00:35:46,193 --> 00:35:48,989
- Yeah. Actually...
- Don't go yet.

892
00:35:49,505 --> 00:35:53,188
Brian, you came through for me
in every way on this case.

893
00:35:53,735 --> 00:35:55,500
And like you said
the other night,

894
00:35:55,541 --> 00:35:57,586
if we don't stop to celebrate
the little things,

895
00:35:57,627 --> 00:35:59,213
then what's any of this for?

896
00:35:59,931 --> 00:36:02,086
I didn't know any better,
I'd say this is your way

897
00:36:02,127 --> 00:36:03,208
of thanking me...

898
00:36:03,852 --> 00:36:05,110
for looking out for you.

899
00:36:05,151 --> 00:36:06,430
It is.

900
00:36:06,579 --> 00:36:08,399
And I happen to have
made us reservations

901
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:10,516
at an amazing place
with live music

902
00:36:10,557 --> 00:36:12,141
in honor of your love of music.

903
00:36:12,182 --> 00:36:14,061
Katrina, I can't tonight.

904
00:36:14,550 --> 00:36:17,471
I really need to get home
with Julie and the baby.

905
00:36:17,512 --> 00:36:18,512
Oh.

906
00:36:19,234 --> 00:36:20,312
The baby. Of course.

907
00:36:20,362 --> 00:36:22,491
I'm sorry, I didn't
think about it.

908
00:36:22,633 --> 00:36:23,772
No, it's okay.

909
00:36:23,813 --> 00:36:25,930
If you don't have one, why
would you think about it?

910
00:36:25,971 --> 00:36:27,641
Right.

911
00:36:28,168 --> 00:36:31,797
But let me just say that I would
love to get a rain check.

912
00:36:33,196 --> 00:36:34,491
Rain check it is.

913
00:36:34,532 --> 00:36:36,241
In the meantime, I gotta go.

914
00:36:38,177 --> 00:36:40,774
I'm sure you have someone else
who would love to take my place.

915
00:36:40,815 --> 00:36:42,055
Oh, of course.

916
00:36:42,784 --> 00:36:44,576
Have a good night, Brian.

917
00:36:45,772 --> 00:36:47,066
Good night, Katrina.

918
00:36:53,701 --> 00:36:54,996
Am I interrupting?

919
00:36:55,122 --> 00:36:56,686
- Not really.
- Good.

920
00:36:56,727 --> 00:36:59,774
Because... I happened to have walked
in on a conversation last night

921
00:36:59,815 --> 00:37:01,758
that made me wanna have
a conversation with you.

922
00:37:01,799 --> 00:37:02,948
I'm listening.

923
00:37:03,301 --> 00:37:04,579
This...

924
00:37:05,064 --> 00:37:08,188
thing between you and Alex
is coming to a head.

925
00:37:08,229 --> 00:37:10,983
Harvey and Louis want Alex
to be the next name partner

926
00:37:11,024 --> 00:37:12,367
and Robert doesn't.

927
00:37:12,408 --> 00:37:14,746
Skip the preamble, Donna.
What's on your mind?

928
00:37:14,967 --> 00:37:16,556
I don't suppose it would
do any good to ask you

929
00:37:16,596 --> 00:37:19,055
to let this go and let Alex
go up there first.

930
00:37:19,096 --> 00:37:20,640
- I don't believe it.
- Believe what?

931
00:37:20,681 --> 00:37:22,204
That Harvey doesn't have
the balls to come in here

932
00:37:22,244 --> 00:37:24,430
and ask me himself.
Instead he sent you.

933
00:37:24,471 --> 00:37:26,501
He didn't send anybody.
I'm here on my own.

934
00:37:26,542 --> 00:37:27,728
Well then you may have internalized

935
00:37:27,768 --> 00:37:29,897
the patriarchal system here,
but I have not.

936
00:37:29,938 --> 00:37:31,727
I haven't internalized anything.

937
00:37:31,768 --> 00:37:34,022
I told you I'm not here
at the behest of any man.

938
00:37:34,063 --> 00:37:36,525
I'm here on my own,
woman to woman,

939
00:37:36,566 --> 00:37:38,716
asking you to take
the long view and wait.

940
00:37:38,757 --> 00:37:40,302
I'm sure you think that's true.

941
00:37:40,343 --> 00:37:42,742
But did it occur to you
to ask Alex to step down

942
00:37:42,783 --> 00:37:43,782
before you came to me?

943
00:37:43,823 --> 00:37:46,110
Because that's what I mean
by patriarchy.

944
00:37:46,151 --> 00:37:48,039
I did think to ask Alex.

945
00:37:48,108 --> 00:37:49,653
And I chose to ask you.

946
00:37:49,919 --> 00:37:51,881
And I did that
because it comes down

947
00:37:51,922 --> 00:37:54,176
to who the promise
was made to first.

948
00:37:54,217 --> 00:37:56,346
Not the gender of the person
it was made to.

949
00:37:56,533 --> 00:37:58,411
What's to stop them
from changing their minds

950
00:37:58,452 --> 00:37:59,873
before it's my turn?

951
00:37:59,914 --> 00:38:01,646
Because they're not gonna
put a second name up there

952
00:38:01,686 --> 00:38:03,354
for at least another year.

953
00:38:05,104 --> 00:38:07,041
What if they put it in writing?

954
00:38:07,639 --> 00:38:09,704
You're a lawyer.
You make it airtight.

955
00:38:10,854 --> 00:38:12,484
You really make a person
get to the bottom

956
00:38:12,524 --> 00:38:14,319
of what's inside of them,
don't you?

957
00:38:14,787 --> 00:38:17,307
- What do you mean?
- When you put it that way,

958
00:38:17,348 --> 00:38:18,955
it's not about them
changing their minds,

959
00:38:18,996 --> 00:38:19,932
or it taking too long,

960
00:38:19,973 --> 00:38:21,861
or even Robert
getting hit by a bus.

961
00:38:22,157 --> 00:38:25,635
The truth is,
I'm not backing down because...

962
00:38:26,946 --> 00:38:29,242
I think I'm better than
Alex Williams.

963
00:38:29,399 --> 00:38:31,691
And I'm not gonna say
that I'm not.

964
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:35,143
Then I respect your decision.

965
00:38:36,317 --> 00:38:37,650
Good night, Samantha.

966
00:38:44,634 --> 00:38:45,838
Hey.

967
00:38:48,455 --> 00:38:50,314
I heard you won your first case.

968
00:38:50,355 --> 00:38:51,823
And the fact that I
already heard about it

969
00:38:51,863 --> 00:38:53,694
means you're making a name
for yourself.

970
00:38:53,735 --> 00:38:55,111
So...

971
00:39:02,094 --> 00:39:03,554
Thank you, Louis.

972
00:39:04,803 --> 00:39:06,848
Wait a second.
Is something wrong?

973
00:39:06,951 --> 00:39:08,675
Goddamn it, did they spell
Bennett with one T again?

974
00:39:08,715 --> 00:39:10,018
No. Nothing's wrong.

975
00:39:10,065 --> 00:39:11,065
It's...

976
00:39:11,171 --> 00:39:13,547
just been a long
day, and I'm tired.

977
00:39:16,877 --> 00:39:19,560
Katrina... ahem... I know you.

978
00:39:19,601 --> 00:39:21,040
You don't get tired
after winning a case.

979
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:22,581
Something is going on.

980
00:39:25,547 --> 00:39:28,814
It's just, I know
I should be happy right now.

981
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:31,932
I finally made it
to the top of the mountain.

982
00:39:31,973 --> 00:39:33,011
I get it.

983
00:39:33,052 --> 00:39:35,962
It only made you realize how much
further you still want to go.

984
00:39:36,207 --> 00:39:38,211
Yes, that's it.

985
00:39:38,725 --> 00:39:40,726
That's exactly it.

986
00:39:42,030 --> 00:39:43,617
No, it's not it.

987
00:39:43,736 --> 00:39:46,346
I have seen that look before,
and it was on my face.

988
00:39:46,404 --> 00:39:47,613
Katrina...

989
00:39:49,086 --> 00:39:51,255
when it comes
to that part of life...

990
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:54,063
you can't force it.

991
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:56,560
It's unpredictable.

992
00:39:58,532 --> 00:40:01,912
- I hate unpredictable.
- I know. I do too.

993
00:40:02,257 --> 00:40:03,319
But...

994
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:05,455
you once told me that someday,

995
00:40:05,496 --> 00:40:07,164
I would find someone.

996
00:40:08,470 --> 00:40:09,727
And I did.

997
00:40:10,082 --> 00:40:11,626
And you will too.

998
00:40:11,972 --> 00:40:13,916
Life is gonna put
that special someone

999
00:40:13,957 --> 00:40:16,128
right in front of you,
and when it happens,

1000
00:40:16,183 --> 00:40:18,225
I know you'll be ready.

1001
00:40:20,992 --> 00:40:22,913
Hey, I just realized,

1002
00:40:23,570 --> 00:40:25,370
I never took you out
to celebrate your promotion.

1003
00:40:25,410 --> 00:40:27,496
What do you say we go out
and get dinner right now?

1004
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:29,158
Another time, Louis.

1005
00:40:29,199 --> 00:40:31,080
I have some work to catch up on.

1006
00:40:52,786 --> 00:40:54,498
Drinking alone?

1007
00:40:54,937 --> 00:40:56,999
I guess what they say is true.

1008
00:40:57,172 --> 00:41:00,096
None of us know
how much time we really have.

1009
00:41:00,229 --> 00:41:01,898
No, we don't.

1010
00:41:02,204 --> 00:41:04,260
Listen, Robert,
I've been doing some thinking

1011
00:41:04,301 --> 00:41:06,472
about the Samantha
and Alex situation.

1012
00:41:06,513 --> 00:41:09,432
Harvey, not tonight.
Just hear me out, please.

1013
00:41:12,995 --> 00:41:15,034
I think we should
let them fight.

1014
00:41:15,591 --> 00:41:18,471
Harvey, we do that, we're
admitting our house is divided.

1015
00:41:18,729 --> 00:41:21,946
And we make it that much easier
for another Tommy Bratton

1016
00:41:21,987 --> 00:41:23,549
to try and pick us apart.

1017
00:41:23,590 --> 00:41:24,729
I know.

1018
00:41:25,385 --> 00:41:26,980
But our house is divided.

1019
00:41:28,130 --> 00:41:30,941
I made a promise.
You made a promise.

1020
00:41:30,982 --> 00:41:32,652
And if we keep doing nothing...

1021
00:41:32,693 --> 00:41:35,410
It's worse than letting them
settle it themselves.

1022
00:41:36,343 --> 00:41:38,679
One case, head-to-head.

1023
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:40,512
Winner gets name partner.

1024
00:41:41,374 --> 00:41:42,672
You think they'll go for it?

1025
00:41:42,713 --> 00:41:44,084
I think they've been
wanting to go at it

1026
00:41:44,124 --> 00:41:45,749
ever since you two got here.

1027
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:52,216
Then I say we let them fight.

1028
00:41:54,156 --> 00:41:56,076
You want to tell them,
or should I?

1029
00:41:56,117 --> 00:41:58,246
Why don't we both tell them?

1030
00:41:58,287 --> 00:41:59,707
But let's do it tomorrow.

1031
00:42:00,065 --> 00:42:00,894
Because after today,

1032
00:42:00,935 --> 00:42:03,481
all I wanna do is
finish this drink,

1033
00:42:03,928 --> 00:42:05,584
go home, and...

1034
00:42:06,402 --> 00:42:08,066
see Laura.

1035
00:42:12,535 --> 00:42:14,328
Good night, Robert.

1036
00:42:19,515 --> 00:42:21,100
Good night, Harvey.

